THE sport of rude barbarian hordes, From their beloved nest

In Greece, of old my first strayed far As exiles, sore distressed.

Tin dear Ausonia's laughing fields Beheld the wanderers come,

And on her hospitable soil Build an enduring home.

Here were uplift their graeeful heads, Here shone their splendors old: Vainly the stranger sought to win The heritage we hold. But tell me, Silvia, if he still Seareh vainly‚ as he roves Beside the Arno' s classic stream In green Italian groves ‘3

My second, King of Latium, held His throne long years ago: Next Umbria, then Etruria came His lawe benign to know; For (if it be no mythic tale The ancient writers tell) A people happy, blithe, content, Wisely he ruled and well.
